result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (2nd) and Operating w/ PAC (2nd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (2nd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (2nd) was dismissed by the court.

  • James A Holzbauer was found guilty of OWI (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Bond previously posted in the amount of $500 has been applied. Remaining fine/costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Same repayment conditions as noted above.

Defendant is entitled to Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges.  Pursuant to s. 346.65(7), Wis. Stats., Defendant shall be required to remain in the County Jail for not less than a 48 consecutive hour period prior to release for huber. The court has no objection to the sentence being served in another jurisdiction.
Prior to re-licensing the defendant is to complete an OWI Assessment.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

Case called @ 2:10 p.m. Defendant James A Holzbauer in court with attorney Todd Allen Snow.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. The parties have reached an agreement.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: Ct 1 - NC.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Ct 2 - Dismissed outright. 15TR1029 & 15TR1030 - DRI. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Sentencing argument by Atty Snow. Exhibit 1 marked. The court returns exhibit 1 to Atty Snow. Statement by DE. Court orders: 10 days WCJ - Huber, GT, No CFTS - Sentence to commence by no later than 12-01-2015, $1379 fine inclusive of costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, $42.50 blood draw cost w/ 60 DTP or PP, 13 mos DL rev/13 mos IID, OWI Assessment, DNA sample and surcharge. Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. The court has no objection to the sentence being served in another jurisdiction. Appeal rights given.
